&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Resuscitation Training Administrator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available within the Resuscitation Team for a motivated and forward thinking individual. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Resuscitation Training Administrator post is integral to the on-going development of the Trust’s Resuscitation Team. You will work with a dedicated management and resuscitation team to provide administration and organisational expertise for this service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You should be motivated, organised, have the required skill set, be an excellent communicator and have the ability to work flexibly. You will support the delivery of future service development and manage resources effectively for the Resuscitation Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If this role appeals to you, and fits your profile, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barbara Knott - Lead Resuscitation Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: barbara.knott@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01553 613165&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Marlow - Lead Resuscitation Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;paul.marlow@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
